{
  "schema": 1,
  "id": "blinds",
  "name": {
    "en": "Venetian Blinds",
    "zh": "百葉窗"
  },
  "desc": {
    "en": "Sun light paired with a blocker. The light passes through the slats and leaves stripes on the character. The blocker does not emit, it only removes part of the light.",
    "zh": "用日光搭配遮擋物，光穿過葉片後在角色身上留下條紋。遮擋物本身不發光，只負責擋掉部分光線。"
  },
  "tip": {
    "en": "The closer the blocker sits to the character, the sharper the stripe edges; further away is softer. Adjusting the blocker's transparency changes how much light passes through, so the shadows never go pure black.",
    "zh": "遮擋物離角色越近，條紋邊緣越銳利，越遠則越模糊；透過調整遮擋物的透明度，可以適當改變光的穿透性，讓陰影不會死黑。"
  },
  "engine_note": null,
